          "body": "Verse 15 is among the most debated in the NT. *But women will be preserved (sozo — saved/preserved) through the bearing of children if they continue in faith and love and sanctity with self-restraint.* Three orthodox readings compete. (1) **The Messiah reading**: *the* childbearing refers to Christ's birth from a woman (Genesis 3:15; Galatians 4:4) — women are saved through the same Christ-event men are. (2) **The sphere reading**: women are spiritually preserved as they walk faithfully in the typical sphere of their calling, including (not limited to) motherhood — a polemic against the proto-Gnostic disparagement of marriage that 4:3 names explicitly. (3) **The protection reading**: women will be physically preserved through the dangers of childbirth as they walk in faith. The sphere reading best fits the immediate context — Paul has just grounded his argument in Genesis 2-3 (where childbearing pain is the curse on Eve), and he is countering false teaching that despised marriage and procreation. Whichever reading is taken, the verse honors what the false teachers despised: marriage, motherhood, and the ordinary callings of the Christian woman."
